&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Picnic&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Picnic is reinventing how people eat at work. We partner with office operators to bring curated, high-quality food options directly to their employees — no cafeterias, no kiosks, no waste. We&#39;ve grown fast, and now we&#39;re building the team to grow even faster by deepening roots in every market we enter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re not looking for a traditional salesperson. We&#39;re looking for someone who becomes the face of Picnic in their city.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Market Manager, you own a metro market end-to-end: from identifying the right office partners and building genuine relationships with decision makers, to ensuring existing customers grow, stay happy, and refer us to others. You&#39;ll be part BD, part account manager, part community builder.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The best Market Managers won&#39;t rely on cold calls or spray-and-pray outreach. They&#39;ll build the kind of local presence where inbound opportunities find them, referrals flow naturally, and customers become advocates. They think strategically, act entrepreneurially, and have an instinct for people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Your Market&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Map your territory: identify target office accounts, gather intel on employee base, decision makers, funding stage, and competitive landscape.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build a presence in your city through events, community touchpoints, and partnerships. Become a known name in the local office and real estate ecosystem.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with local hotels, coworking spaces, and venues to generate warm leads and high-value referral pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grow the Book&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert inbound leads and referrals into Picnic customers. Run discovery conversations, pilot launches, and onboardings with care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nurture relationships with lapsed customers who are ready to give Picnic another shot.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive expansion within existing accounts: new locations, new employee cohorts, new features, new concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Keep Customers Thriving&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the customer relationship post-launch: deliver monthly usage reports, share insights, and surface opportunities to improve their Picnic experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary escalation point for high-stakes support issues. Be the person your customers trust to get things resolved.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track defects, mitigations, and satisfaction scores; synthesize feedback into clear signals for the Picnic product and ops teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive feature adoption and help POCs champion Picnic internally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Generate Referrals &amp;amp; Amplify the Brand&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively cultivate referrals from happy customers. This is one of our highest-value GTM levers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent Picnic at local events, industry gatherings, and informal happy hours to build pipeline through relationships, not cold volume.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to Picnic&#39;s local presence through social content and community storytelling where applicable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who You Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You&#39;re a people magnet. Relationships are your superpower. People trust you quickly, and you maintain that trust over time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You think like an owner. You don&#39;t wait for leads to be handed to you. You understand your market, spot opportunities, and move on them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&

